{"author":{"id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=","is_bot":false,"login":"konard","name":"Konstantin Diachenko"},"body":"## Summary\n\nOptimizes `$mol_charset_ucf` encode/decode functions for better performance while maintaining code clarity.\n\n### Key optimizations:\n\n- **Move `high()` helper to module level**: Avoids closure creation per function call, reducing GC pressure\n- **Remove inline closures**: `write_high`, `write_remap`, `write_mode`, `read_remap` were closures defined inside functions - replaced with inline code or module-level function\n- **Use array + join for decode**: Changed `text +=` to `result.push()` + `result.join('')` for faster string building\n- **Merge conditions in ASCII branch**: `if( mode !== tiny_mode ) { if( !fast ) ... }` → `if( mode !== tiny_mode && !ascii_map[ code ] )` for better branch prediction\n- **Fix typo**: `tine_limit` → `tiny_limit`\n\n### Performance improvements:\n\n- **Encode**: Faster due to no closure creation and optimized conditional checks\n- **Decode**: Faster due to `array.push()` + `join('')` instead of `string +=` concatenation\n\n### Test plan\n\n- [x] All existing UCF tests pass (`mol_charset_ucf` CI success)\n- [x] Encoding/decoding produces identical results to original implementation\n- [x] No breaking changes to the public API\n\n### CI Status Note\n\nThe `mol_vary` test failure is a **pre-existing issue on master branch** (not caused by this PR). The same test fails on master with identical error:\n- Test: `vary pack text` at `vary/vary.test.tsx:139`\n- Expected: `Uint8Array(6) [ 164, 136, 218, 219, 220, 248 ]`\n- Actual: `Uint8Array(6) [ 165, 136, 218, 219, 220, 248 ]`\n\nThis is due to incorrect test expectation - the UCF encoding of 'абв' produces 5 bytes (`text|5`), not 4 bytes (`text|4`).\n\nFixes hyoo-ru/mam_mol#826\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)","closedAt":"2026-01-08T08:41:46Z","comments":[{"id":"IC_kwDOA3vPgs7d4QBQ","author":{"login":"konard"},"authorAssociation":"CON