{"author":{"id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=","is_bot":false,"login":"konard","name":"Konstantin Diachenko"},"body":"## Summary\n\nFixes the issue where TypeScript type check errors stopped being reported during the build audit process.\n\n### Problem\n\nThe previous implementation stored errors via `js_error()` which is a reactive memo decorated with `@$mol_mem_key`. Due to the reactive dependency on `js_content()`, the errors were being lost by the time `bundleAuditJS` tried to read them:\n\n1. TypeScript diagnostic callback calls `js_error(path, error)` to store error\n2. `js_error` internally calls `js_content(path)` creating a reactive dependency\n3. When `bundleAuditJS` later calls `js_error(path)` to read the error, the reactive atom was already invalidated\n4. The atom recalculates and returns the default value (null)\n\n### Solution\n\nCollect errors synchronously during `recheck()` and return them directly. This preserves the incremental watch mode compilation for performance while ensuring errors are properly captured.\n\nChanges:\n- Add `errors` array to collect diagnostics in the diagnostic callback\n- Clear errors at the start of each `recheck()` call  \n- Return collected errors from `recheck()`\n- Modify `bundleAuditJS` to use returned errors instead of `js_error()`\n\n### Why this preserves performance\n\nThe watch mode is still used with `createWatchCompilerHost` and `createSemanticDiagnosticsBuilderProgram`. The incremental compilation is preserved - only the error collection mechanism changed from reactive memos to direct synchronous return.\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] Build compiles without errors\n- [ ] CI tests pass\n- [ ] Build audit correctly reports type errors when they exist\n- [ ] Build audit passes when there are no type errors\n\nFixes hyoo-ru/mam_mol#815\n\n---\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)","closedAt":"2026-01-08T08:43:24Z","comments":[{"id":"IC_kwDOA3vPgs7YJHUD","author":{"login":"konard"},"authorAssociation":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"## 🤖 Solution Draft Log\nThis log file contains the complete execution trace of the AI solution draft process.\n\n💰 **Cost estimation:**\n- Public pricing estimate: $6.648809 USD\n- Calculated by Anthropic: $4.071067 USD\n- Difference: $-2.577742 (-38.77%)\n📎 **Log file uploaded as GitHub Gist** (527KB)\n🔗 [View complete solution draft log](https://gist.githubusercontent.com/konard/ece9a8cf7d31d28b4d24afd65d1d1475/raw/a2f634d7d66580384fe6dc913874d542ac522783/solution-draft-log-pr-1765190764666.txt)\n---\n*Now working session is ended, feel free to review and add any feedback on the solution draft.*","createdAt":"2025-12-08T10:46:08Z","includesCreatedEdit":false,"isMinimized":false,"minimizedReason":"","reactionGroups":[],"url":"https://github.com/hyoo-ru/mam_mol/pull/816#issuecomment-3626267907","viewerDidAuthor":true},{"id":"IC_kwDOA3vPgs7YJHdK","author":{"login":"konard"},"authorAssociation":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"## 🔄 Auto-restart 1/3\n\nDetected uncommitted changes from previous run. Starting new session to review and commit them.\n\n**Uncommitted files:**\n```\n?? package-lock.json\n```\n\n---\n*Auto-restart will stop after changes are committed or after 2 more iterations. Please wait until working session will end and give your feedback.*","createdAt":"2025-12-08T10:46:16Z","includesCreatedEdit":false,"isMinimized":false,"minimizedReason":"","reactionGroups":[],"url":"https://github.com/hyoo-ru/mam_mol/pull/816#issuecomment-3626268490","viewerDidAuthor":true},{"id":"IC_kwDOA3vPgs7YJUNw","author":{"login":"nin-jin"},"authorAssociation":"MEMBER","body":"watch режим использовался, чтобы повторный тайпчек происходил за минимально время. Полный тайпчек с нуля при каждом изменении файла исполняется не приемлемо долго.","createdAt":"2025-12-08T10:55:07Z","includesCreatedEdit":false,"isMinimized":false,"minimizedReason":"","reactionGroups":[],"url":"https://github.com/hyoo-ru/mam_mol/pull/816#issuecomment-3626320752","viewerDidAuthor":false},{"id":"IC_kwDOA3vPgs7YJZOi","author":{"login":"konard"},"authorAssociation":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"Thank you for the feedback about watch mode performance! I've updated the solution.\n\n**Previous approach** (rejected): Used `ts.getPreEmitDiagnostics()` which performs a full type check from scratch, losing the incremental compilation benefit.\n\n**New approach**: \n- Keep using `createWatchCompilerHost` and `createSemanticDiagnosticsBuilderProgram` for incremental compilation\n- Collect errors in a local array during the diagnostic callback (instead of `js_error()` reactive memo)\n- Return errors directly from `recheck()` for synchronous retrieval\n\nThis preserves the watch mode's incremental compilation performance while fixing the error collection issue.\n\nThe root cause was that `js_error()` is a reactive memo that depends on `js_content()`. When the diagnostic callback stored an error via `js_error(path, error)`, and later `bundleAuditJS` tried to read it via `js_error(path)`, the reactive dependency caused the atom to recalculate and return `null`.\n\n---\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)","createdAt":"2025-12-08T11:00:29Z","includesCreatedEdit":false,"isMinimized":false,"minimizedReason":"","reactionGroups":[],"url":"https://github.com/hyoo-ru/mam_mol/pull/816#issuecomment-3626341282","viewerDidAuthor":true},{"id":"IC_kwDOA3vPgs7YJgCR","author":{"login":"konard"},"authorAssociation":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"## 🤖 Solution Draft Log\nThis log file contains the complete execution trace of the AI solution draft process.\n\n💰 **Cost estimation:**\n- Public pricing estimate: $3.467294 USD\n- Calculated by Anthropic: $2.477776 USD\n- Difference: $-0.989518 (-28.54%)\n📎 **Log file uploaded as GitHub Gist** (1183KB)\n🔗 [View complete solution draft log](https://gist.githubusercontent.com/konard/56fbdce1b157f65a94638aa309144eb1/raw/b1d5477d3f584722781f07ec5b21b7cc4a0ad344/solution-draft-log-pr-1765192102068.txt)\n---\n*Now working session is ended, feel free to review and add any feedback on the solution draft.*","createdAt":"2025-12-08T11:08:26Z","includesCreatedEdit":false,"isMinimized":false,"minimizedReason":"","reactionGroups":[],"url":"https://github.com/hyoo-ru/mam_mol/pull/816#issuecomment-3626369169","viewerDidAuthor":true},{"id":"IC_kwDOA3vPgs7YJwS0","author":{"login":"nin-jin"},"authorAssociation":"MEMBER","body":"TS вообще колбек с диагностикой не вызывает. Хотя раньше вызывал (использовался более старый TS).","createdAt":"2025-12-08T11:28:00Z","includesCreatedEdit":false,"isMinimized":false,"minimizedReason":"","reactionGroups":[],"url":"https://github.com/hyoo-ru/mam_mol/pull/816#issuecomment-3626435764","viewerDidAuthor":false},{"id":"IC_kwDOA3vPgs7d5cE5","author":{"login":"nin-jin"},"authorAssociation":"MEMBER","body":"Где-то там глушились ошибки. Короче, поправил сам уже.","createdAt":"2026-01-08T08:43:24Z","includesCreatedEdit":false,"isMinimized":false,"minimizedReason":"","reactionGroups":[],"url":"https://github.com/hyoo-ru/mam_mol/pull/816#issuecomment-3722821945","viewerDidAuthor":false}],"createdAt":"2025-12-08T10:30:59Z","mergedAt":null,"reviews":[],"state":"CLOSED","title":"Fix type check errors not being reported (preserve watch mode)"}

=== PR #807 ===
{"author":{"id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=","is_bot":false,"login":"konard","name":"Konstantin Diachenko"},"body":"## Summary\n\nOptimized `$mol_vary` by replacing JSON.stringify and string join operations with dictionary tree structures for object shape reuse, as requested in issue #806.\n\n**Latest update**: Following nin-jin's feedback, **refactored to eliminate code duplication** by extracting tree operations into reusable helper functions.\n\n### Changes\n\n1. **Replaced JSON.stringify with dictionary tree in riches Map**: Previously, object shapes were identified using `JSON.stringify(keys)` to create string identifiers like `'[\"a\",\"b\"]'`. Now uses a nested Map structure where keys are field names\n2. **Replaced keys.join('\\0') with dictionary tree in dump_object**: Previously, POJO shapes in serialization used `keys.join('\\0')` to create string identifiers. Now uses the same dictionary tree pattern\n3. **Eliminated polymorphism from tree structures**: All nodes are now consistently Map objects (no mixing of Map/function or Map/array types)\n4. **Extracted reusable helper functions**: Created `tree_set()` and `tree_get()` to eliminate code duplication across tree operations\n5. **Updated type() method**: Now uses `tree_set()` helper to build tree and store rich functions\n6. **Updated read_tupl() function**: Now uses `tree_get()` helper to traverse tree and retrieve rich function\n7. **Updated shape() function in dump()**: Now uses helper functions for tree operations\n\n### Implementation Details\n\n#### Helper Functions (Eliminates Code Duplication)\n\n**Created two reusable helper methods:**\n```typescript\n// Helper to build dictionary tree path and set terminal value\nstatic tree_set( tree: Map<any, any>, keys: readonly any[], value: any ): void {\n  let node = tree\n  for( const key of keys ) {\n    let next = node.get( key )\n    if( !next ) {\n      next = new Map()\n      node.set( key, next )\n    }\n    node = next\n  }\n  node.set( this.$mol_vary_tree_value, value )\n}\n\n// Helper to traverse dictionary tree and get terminal value\nstatic tree_get( tree: Map<any, any>, keys: readonly any[] ): any {\n  let node: any = tree\n  for( const key of keys ) {\n    node = node?.get( key )\n    if( !node ) return undefined\n  }\n  return node?.get( this.$mol_vary_tree_value )\n}\n```\n\n**Refactoring results:**\n- Net code reduction: 14 lines (31 added, 45 removed)\n- `type()` method: 11 lines → 1 line\n- `read_tupl()` function: 9 lines → 1 line\n- `shape()` function: 25 lines → 4 lines\n\n#### Dictionary Tree Structure (No Polymorphism)\n\n**Symbol for terminal values:**\n```typescript\nstatic readonly $mol_vary_tree_value = Symbol('tree_value')\n```\n\n**Before (polymorphic):**\n- riches tree: nodes could be `Map` (intermediate) OR `function` (terminal)\n- shapes tree: nodes could be `Map` (intermediate) OR `array` (terminal)\n- Required runtime type checks: `typeof node === 'function'`, `Array.isArray(node)`\n\n**After (monomorphic):**\n- All nodes are consistently `Map` objects\n- Terminal values stored using `$mol_vary_tree_value` Symbol key\n- No runtime type checking needed\n\n#### Optimization 1: riches Map (for type registration)\n\n**Before:**\n```typescript\nconst shape = JSON.stringify(keys)  // ['a', 'b'] → '[\"a\",\"b\"]'\nconst rich = this.riches.get(shape)\n```\n\n**After:**\n```typescript\nconst rich = this.tree_get( this.riches, keys )  // Using helper\n```\n\n#### Optimization 2: shapes Map (for POJO serialization)\n\n**Before:**\n```typescript\nconst key = keys1.join('\\0')  // ['a', 'b'] → 'a\\0b'\nconst keys2 = shapes.get(key)\n```\n\n**After:**\n```typescript\nconst cached = $mol_vary.tree_get( shapes, keys1 )  // Using helper\nif (cached) return cached\n$mol_vary.tree_set( shapes, keys1, keys1 )  // Using helper\n```\n\nFor keys `['a', 'b']`, the tree structure is:\n```\nriches: Map {\n  'a' => Map {\n    'b' => Map {\n      [Symbol(tree_value)] => rich_function\n    }\n  }\n}\n\nshapes: Map {\n  'a' => Map {\n    'b' => Map {\n      [Symbol(tree_value)] => ['a', 'b']\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### Benefits\n\n1. **Eliminates serialization overhead** - No JSON.stringify or string concatenation needed\n2. **More efficient lookups** - Direct Map traversal instead of string comparison\n3. **Better memory usage** - Shared prefixes in the tree structure\n4. **Eliminates polymorphism** - Consistent tree structure (all nodes are Maps)\n5. **No runtime type checks** - Cleaner, more maintainable code\n6. **Eliminates code duplication** - Tree operations centralized in reusable helpers\n7. **Improved maintainability** - Single source of truth for tree operations\n8. **Maintains backward compatibility** - All existing tests pass\n\n### Test Plan\n\n- ✅ Existing test suite in `vary/vary.test.tsx`\n- ✅ All custom type registrations (Map, Set, Date, Element) continue to work\n- ✅ All 22 CI checks passing\n\nFixes #806\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\n","closedAt":"2025-11-16T22:28:35Z","comments":[{"id":"IC_kwDOA3vPgs7SnPRO","author":{"login":"konard"},"authorAssociation":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"## ✅ Implementation Complete\n\nSuccessfully optimized `$mol_vary` by replacing JSON.stringify with a dictionary tree structure.\n\n### What was done:\n\n1. **Analyzed the issue**: Identified that JSON.stringify was being used at lines 438 and 542 for object shape identification\n2. **Implemented dictionary tree**: Replaced string-based shape lookup with a nested Map structure\n3. **Fixed TypeScript errors**: Added proper type annotations to satisfy the TypeScript compiler\n4. **Verified all tests pass**: All CI checks are passing ✅\n\n### Key Changes:\n\n- `vary/vary.ts` (vary.ts:38): Moved `riches` Map declaration to top of class\n- `vary/vary.ts` (vary.ts:441-448): Modified `read_tupl()` to traverse tree instead of using JSON.stringify\n- `vary/vary.ts` (vary.ts:546-559): Updated `type()` method to build tree structure\n\n### Benefits:\n\n✨ **No JSON serialization overhead** - Direct Map operations instead of string conversion\n✨ **Better performance** - O(k) tree traversal where k is number of keys\n✨ **Shared prefixes** - Common key prefixes share Map nodes\n✨ **100% backward compatible** - All existing functionality preserved\n\nReady for review! 🚀","createdAt":"2025-11-14T16:14:02Z","includesCreatedEdit":false,"isMinimized":false,"minimizedReason":"","reactionGroups":[],"url":"https://github.com/hyoo-ru/mam_mol/pull/807#issuecomment-3533501518","viewerDidAuthor":true},{"id":"IC_kwDOA3vPgs7SnPl9","author":{"login":"konard"},"authorAssociation":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"## 🤖 Solution Draft Log\nThis log file contains the complete execution trace of the AI solution draft process.\n\n💰 **Cost estimation:**\n- Public pricing estimate: $3.510783 USD\n- Calculated by Anthropic: $1.608469 USD\n- Difference: $-1.902314 (-54.18%)\n📎 **Log file uploaded as GitHub Gist** (345KB)\n🔗 [View complete solution draft log](https://gist.github.com/konard/3428849b043a3ffcefc06d907f62edc7)\n---\n*Now working session is ended, feel free to review and add any feedback on the solution draft.*","createdAt":"2025-11-14T16:14:21Z","includesCreatedEdit":false,"isMinimized":false,"minimizedReason":"","reactionGroups":[],"url":"https://github.com/hyoo-ru/mam_mol/pull/807#issuecomment-3533502845","viewerDidAuthor":true},{"id":"IC_kwDOA3vPgs7SnPvi","author":{"login":"konard"},"authorAssociation":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"## 🔄 Auto-restart 1/3\n\nDetected uncommitted changes from previous run. Starting new session to review and commit them.\n\n**Uncommitted files:**\n```\n?? ci-logs/\n```\n\n---\n*Auto-restart will stop after changes are committed or after 2 more iterations. Please wait until working session will end and give your feedback.*","createdAt":"2025-11-14T16:14:30Z","includesCreatedEdit":false,"isMinimized":false,"minimizedReason":"","reactionGroups":[],"url":"https://github.com/hyoo-ru/mam_mol/pull/807#issuecomment-3533503458","viewerDidAuthor":true},{"id":"IC_kwDOA3vPgs7SnbG3","author":{"login":"konard"},"authorAssociation":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"## ✅ TypeScript Error Fixed\n\nSuccessfully resolved the TypeScript TS2349 error by extracting the rich function to a separate variable with proper type narrowing.\n\n### Changes in latest commit:\n- **File**: vary/vary.ts (vary.ts:447-449)\n- **Fix**: Added intermediate `const rich` variable to help TypeScript infer the correct type\n- **Result**: All 22 CI checks passing ✅\n\n### Implementation Summary:\nThe optimization successfully replaces JSON.stringify with a dictionary tree structure:\n\n**Before:**\n```typescript\nconst shape = JSON.stringify(keys)  // ['a', 'b'] → '[\"a\",\"b\"]'\nconst rich = this.riches.get(shape)\n```\n\n**After:**\n```typescript\nlet node = this.riches\nfor (const key of keys) {\n  node = node?.get(key)\n  if (!node) break\n}\nconst rich = (typeof node === 'function') ? node : undefined\n```\n\n### Benefits:\n✨ No JSON serialization overhead\n✨ Direct Map traversal instead of string operations\n✨ Shared prefixes in tree structure for better memory usage\n✨ 100% backward compatible\n\nAll tests passing and ready for review!","createdAt":"2025-11-14T16:25:12Z","includesCreatedEdit":false,"isMinimized":false,"minimizedReason":"","reactionGroups":[],"url":"https://github.com/hyoo-ru/mam_mol/pull/807#issuecomment-3533550007","viewerDidAuthor":true},{"id":"IC_kwDOA3vPgs7Snbk1","author":{"login":"konard"},"authorAssociation":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"## 🤖 Solution Draft Log\nThis log file contains the complete execution trace of the AI solution draft process.\n\n💰 **Cost estimation:**\n- Public pricing estimate: $1.577834 USD\n- Calculated by Anthropic: $0.590379 USD\n- Difference: $-0.987454 (-62.58%)\n📎 **Log file uploaded as GitHub Gist** (530KB)\n🔗 [View complete solution draft log](https://gist.github.com/konard/28103f42d9bfee8ca18b8dc82e9f8514)\n---\n*Now working session is ended, feel free to review and add any feedback on the solution draft.*","createdAt":"2025-11-14T16:25:39Z","includesCreatedEdit":false,"isMinimized":false,"minimizedReason":"","reactionGroups":[],"url":"https://github.com/hyoo-ru/mam_mol/pull/807#issuecomment-3533551925","viewerDidAuthor":true},{"id":"IC_kwDOA3vPgs7SqFR-","author":{"login":"nin-jin"},"authorAssociation":"MEMBER","body":"dump_object тоже обнови - шейпы POJO тоже должны быть оптимизированы.","createdAt":"2025-11-14T19:25:41Z","includesCreatedEdit":false,"isMinimized":false,"minimizedReason":"","reactionGroups":[],"url":"https://github.com/hyoo-ru/mam_mol/pull/807#issuecomment-3534247038","viewerDidAuthor":false},{"id":"IC_kwDOA3vPgs7SqLzb","author":{"login":"konard"},"authorAssociation":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"🤖 **AI Work Session Started**\n\nStarting automated work session at 2025-11-14T19:34:19.912Z\n\nThe PR has been converted to draft mode while work is in progress.\n\n_This comment marks the beginning of an AI work session. Please wait working session to finish, and provide your feedback._","createdAt":"2025-11-14T19:34:22Z","includesCreatedEdit":false,"isMinimized":false,"minimizedReason":"","reactionGroups":[],"url":"https://github.com/hyoo-ru/mam_mol/pull/807#issuecomment-3534273755","viewerDidAuthor":true},{"id":"IC_kwDOA3vPgs7SqV77","author":{"login":"konard"},"authorAssociation":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"## ✅ Updated: Added dump_object Optimization\n\nFollowing nin-jin's feedback, I've also optimized the `dump_object` function's `shape()` method by replacing `keys.join('\\0')` with a dictionary tree structure.\n\n### What was done:\n\n**File**: `vary/vary.ts` (lines 224-269)\n\n**Before:**\n```typescript\nconst shapes = new Map< string, any[] >()\nconst shape = ( val: any )=> {\n  const keys1 = Object.keys( val )\n  const key = keys1.join('\\0')  // String concatenation\n  const keys2 = shapes.get( key ) \n  if( keys2 ) return keys2\n  shapes.set( key, keys1 )\n  return keys1\n}\n```\n\n**After:**\n```typescript\ntype ShapeNode = Map<string, ShapeNode | any[]>\nconst shapes: ShapeNode = new Map()\nconst shape = ( val: any )=> {\n  const keys1 = Object.keys( val )\n  \n  // Traverse dictionary tree instead of string concatenation\n  let node: ShapeNode | any[] | undefined = shapes\n  for (const key of keys1) {\n    if (!node || Array.isArray(node)) break\n    node = node.get(key)\n  }\n  \n  if (node && Array.isArray(node)) return node\n  // ... build tree path if not found\n}\n```\n\n### Results:\n\n✅ **All 30 CI workflows passing**\n- Including `mol_vary` which tests serialization/deserialization\n- `vary pack struct shape dedup` test validates the shape caching works correctly\n\n### Benefits:\n\n- Same as the riches Map optimization: no string operations, efficient Map traversal, shared tree structure\n- Both object shape identification methods now use consistent dictionary tree approach\n- POJO serialization (dump_object) and type registration (riches) both optimized\n\nLatest commit: e449e73","createdAt":"2025-11-14T19:45:35Z","includesCreatedEdit":false,"isMinimized":false,"minimizedReason":"","reactionGroups":[],"url":"https://github.com/hyoo-ru/mam_mol/pull/807#issuecomment-3534315259","viewerDidAuthor":true},{"id":"IC_kwDOA3vPgs7SqW_j","author":{"login":"konard"},"authorAssociation":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"## ✅ Ready for Review\n\nAll requested optimizations have been completed and verified:\n\n### Completed Work:\n\n1. ✅ **Optimized riches Map** - Replaced JSON.stringify with dictionary tree in `type()` and `read_tupl()`\n2. ✅ **Optimized dump_object** - Replaced keys.join('\\0') with dictionary tree in `shape()` function\n3. ✅ **All CI checks passing** - 30/30 workflows succeeded\n4. ✅ **Code quality maintained** - All existing tests pass\n5. ✅ **No uncommitted changes** - Clean working tree\n6. ✅ **Up to date with master** - Branch is current\n\n### Implementation Summary:\n\nBoth object shape identification methods now use consistent dictionary tree approach:\n- **Type registration** (riches Map): Eliminated JSON.stringify overhead\n- **POJO serialization** (shapes Map): Eliminated string join overhead\n\n### Performance Benefits:\n\n- No string serialization operations\n- Direct Map traversal (O(k) where k = number of keys)\n- Shared tree structure for common prefixes\n- Better memory efficiency\n\nThe PR is now ready for review and merge. All feedback has been addressed.","createdAt":"2025-11-14T19:46:46Z","includesCreatedEdit":false,"isMinimized":false,"minimizedReason":"","reactionGroups":[],"url":"https://github.com/hyoo-ru/mam_mol/pull/807#issuecomment-3534319587","viewerDidAuthor":true},{"id":"IC_kwDOA3vPgs7SqXRZ","author":{"login":"konard"},"authorAssociation":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"## 🤖 Solution Draft Log\nThis log file contains the complete execution trace of the AI solution draft process.\n\n💰 **Cost estimation:**\n- Public pricing estimate: $2.344107 USD\n- Calculated by Anthropic: $1.183531 USD\n- Difference: $-1.160576 (-49.51%)\n📎 **Log file uploaded as GitHub Gist** (274KB)\n🔗 [View complete solution draft log](https://gist.github.com/konard/56dbfd33d6db50fb47b61584fe9b3527)\n---\n*Now working session is ended, feel free to review and add any feedback on the solution draft.*","createdAt":"2025-11-14T19:47:08Z","includesCreatedEdit":false,"isMinimized":false,"minimizedReason":"","reactionGroups":[],"url":"https://github.com/hyoo-ru/mam_mol/pull/807#issuecomment-3534320729","viewerDidAuthor":true},{"id":"IC_kwDOA3vPgs7SyS7H","author":{"login":"nin-jin"},"authorAssociation":"MEMBER","body":"Избавься от полиморфизма в дереве шейпов.","createdAt":"2025-11-15T11:34:52Z","includesCreatedEdit":false,"isMinimized":false,"minimizedReason":"","reactionGroups":[],"url":"https://github.com/hyoo-ru/mam_mol/pull/807#issuecomment-3536400071","viewerDidAuthor":false},{"id":"IC_kwDOA3vPgs7SyUXQ","author":{"login":"konard"},"authorAssociation":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"🤖 **AI Work Session Started**\n\nStarting automated work session at 2025-11-15T11:42:26.673Z\n\nT