{"author":{"id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=","is_bot":false,"login":"konard","name":"Konstantin Diachenko"},"body":"## Summary\nImplements focusable legend items that highlight the corresponding graph when clicked, following architectural guidance to use \\$mol_switch and avoid adding properties to individual graphs.\n\n### Changes\n- **Uses \\$mol_switch**: Manages focused graph state using the standard switch component\n- **No modifications to \\$mol_plot**: All functionality isolated to \\$mol_chart components\n- **No properties added to graphs**: Color control done via dynamic method override in pane\n- **Legend items remain clickable buttons**: Visual UI separate from state management\n- **Focus state management**: \\`graph_focused?\\` property (string, empty for no focus) managed by switch\n- **Visual highlight**: Focused graph highlighted with accent color (lightness 50% vs 35%)\n- **Toggle behavior**: Clicking a legend item again unfocuses the graph\n\n### Implementation details\n1. \\$mol_chart_legend contains both a \\$mol_switch (for state) and clickable buttons (for UI)\n2. \\$mol_switch manages \\`graph_focused?\\` as a string (graph index or empty string)\n3. \\$mol_chart_pane overrides graph \\`color()\\` methods dynamically during \\`graphs_colored()\\`\n4. State flows from switch through chart to pane to graph color calculations\n5. **No modifications to \\$mol_plot components** - all functionality isolated to \\$mol_chart\n\n### Testing\nThe changes should be visible in the chart demo where clicking on legend items will highlight the corresponding graph line.\n\nFixes #345\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.ai/code)","closedAt":null,"comments":[{"id":"IC_kwDOA3vPgs7ILWFW","author":{"login":"konard"},"authorAssociation":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"## 🤖 Solution Draft Log\n\nThis log file contains the complete execution trace of the AI solution draft process.\n\n📎 **Log file uploaded as GitHub Gist** (281KB)\n🔗 [View complete solution draft log](ht