=== PR #785 ===
{"author":{"id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=","is_bot":false,"login":"konard","name":"Konstantin Diachenko"},"body":"## Summary\n\nThis PR fixes the issue where email input fields on mobile devices show a regular keyboard instead of an email-specific keyboard with easy access to @ symbol and .com shortcuts.\n\n### Changes Made\n\n- ✅ Created new `$mol_email` component that extends `$mol_string`\n  - Sets `type` to `'email'` for proper HTML5 email input\n  - Sets `keyboard` to `'email'` for better mobile input experience\n- ✅ Updated `$mol_bar` demo to use `$mol_email` instead of `$mol_string` for email fields\n\n### Problem Solved\n\nPreviously, when users focused on email input fields in the $mol_bar demo on mobile devices (iOS Safari, Windows Mobile Edge, etc.), they would see a regular keyboard. This made it inconvenient to type email addresses as the @ symbol was not easily accessible.\n\nWith this fix, mobile devices will now show an email-specific keyboard that includes:\n- Easy access to @ symbol\n- .com shortcuts\n- Email-optimized layout\n\n### Testing\n\nThe changes have been implemented according to the $mol framework patterns:\n- The new component follows the same structure as other input components like `$mol_password` and `$mol_phone`\n- The demo has been updated to use the new component\n\nFixes #196\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.ai/code)\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>","closedAt":"2025-09-29T14:13:32Z","comments":[{"id":"IC_kwDOA3vPgs7HdeCa","author":{"login":"konard"},"authorAssociation":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"## 🤖 Solution Draft Log\n\nThis log file contains the complete execution trace of the AI solution draft process.\n\n📎 **Log file uploaded as GitHub Gist** (197KB)\n🔗 [View complete solution draft log](https://gist.github.com/konard/dc446dc215591a9c821ecd6a7c089fad)\n\n---\n*Log automatically attached by solve.mjs with --attach-logs option*","createdAt":"2025-09-29T11:18:56Z","includesCreatedEdit":false,"isMinimize